<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-06-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-06-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="377" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d377">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 Czechoslovakia/188a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in Czechoslovakia (<persName type="to">Hibbard</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 165</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-06-27">June 27,
                                    1932</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The Secretary of State refers to previous correspondence regarding
                                the President’s Proposal of June 20, 1931, for postponement of
                                intergovernmental debts and transmits for the information of the
                                American Chargé d’Affaires copy of the “Agreement between the
                                Czechoslovak Republic and the United States of America, June 10,
                                    1932”.<note n="25" xml:id="d377fn25">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Annual Report of the Secretary of the
                                        Treasury</hi>, 1932, pp. 299–300.</note>
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>